      "question": "I Have a Hold, How Can I Obtain Documentation I Completed My Degree?",
      "answer_paragraphs": [
        "If you have a Student Accounting hold on your account, you can still obtain a letter indicating you completed your degree at Illinois Tech. Here are the steps you can complete to obtain this official letter of completion:",
        "Visit the National Student Clearinghouse website: mystudentcenter.org/. You can obtain the letter required for the visa by going to the alumnus picture, and selecting \"verify my degree/past attendance.\"You can also go to this link directly too: https://secure.studentclearinghouse.org/vs/Index.Once you are on the Verification Services page, you will need to select the option \"Degree or School Certificate\", then enter your personal information."
      ],
      "full_answer": "If you have a Student Accounting hold on your account, you can still obtain a letter indicating you completed your degree at Illinois Tech. Here are the steps you can complete to obtain this official letter of completion: Visit the National Student Clearinghouse website: mystudentcenter.org/. You can obtain the letter required for the visa by going to the alumnus picture, and selecting \"verify my degree/past attendance.\"You can also go to this link directly too: https://secure.studentclearinghouse.org/vs/Index.Once you are on the Verification Services page, you will need to select the option \"Degree or School Certificate\", then enter your personal information.",
